# Definition 3.3.1 (Functions). Let X,Y be sets, and let P(x,y) be a property pertaining to an object x ∈ X and an object y ∈ Y , such that for every x ∈ X, there is exactly one y ∈ Y for which P(x,y) is true (this is sometimes known as the vertical line test). Then we define the function f : X → Y defined by P on the domain X and range Y to be the object which, given any input x ∈ X, assigns an output f(x) ∈ Y , defined to be the unique object f(x) for which P(x,f(x)) is true. Thus, for any x ∈ X and y ∈ Y ,
# y=f(x) ⇐⇒ P(x,y)istrue.

