Lemma 3.3.12 (Composition is associative). Let f : Z → W , g : Y → Z,andh:X→Y befunctions. Thenf◦(g◦h)=(f◦g)◦h.
Proof. Sinceg◦hisafunctionfromXtoZ,f◦(g◦h)isafunctionfrom X to W. Similarly f ◦g is a function from Y to W, and hence (f ◦g)◦h is a function from X to W. Thus f ◦(g◦h) and (f ◦g)◦h have the same domain and range. In order to check that they are equal, we see from Definition 3.3.7 that we have to verify that (f ◦(g◦h))(x) = ((f ◦g)◦h)(x) for all x ∈ X. But by Definition 3.3.10
as desired.
(f ◦ (g ◦ h))(x) = f((g ◦ h)(x)) = f(g(h(x))
= (f ◦ g)(h(x)) = ((f ◦ g) ◦ h)(x)

